USD240.ORG
www.usd240.org

Twin Valley Usd 240
September 4 at 4:25 PM ·

ALL USD 240 Students - Food Service Announcement

The USDA made an announcement this week stating schools could provide a free breakfast and lunch to ALL students regardless of their status from now until December 31, or when the state/federal funding runs out. We have applied for the waiver and have been approved to begin providing this service to all students starting September 4. No lunch accounts will be charged until this funding source is no longer available.

We will not reimburse lunch account funds at this time as those dollars will be used once this program is over.

Because of other funding programs, we still request you complete the free/reduced application form and submit to your school as soon as possible. These reports assist in funding Title and At-Risk services and add additional dollars to our schools. Application Link: https://www.usd240.org/vimages/shared/vnews/stories/594930b04f342/20-21%20HouseholdApplication.pdf

Have a great day!

Pam Irwin

Superintendent

post_text:
A few reminders from the ReOpening Playbook that are important for getting the day started tomorrow morning:

Bus riders will have their temperature taken prior to getting on the bus. All others will have their temperature taken outside the Activity Entrance at the school.

Only bus riders will enter through the Main Entrance. Everyone else enters through the Activity Entrance

GS students will report directly to their classroom. JH/HS students will report directly to their Block 1 classroom.

Students will be released from their classrooms to get breakfast in the cafeteria. For JH/HS students, this is also when they would take their fresh practice clothes to the locker room.

shared_text:
Twin Valley Usd 240
August 20 at 5:40 PM ·

USD 240 has the option to order additional masks for students, however we don't want to submit this order if everyone already has enough masks. These masks would be in addition to the school specific masks we have coming for each school, and will be a generic color not specific to a school.

Please add a comment if you are interested. If there is enough interest, we will submit an order. We will have the disposable masks available until our orders arrive.

UPDATE: Our intentions are to order these masks if there are enough students that still need a mask or two. We are using covid funds to make the purchase so we will not be allowed to sell them. They will be available for those that need them.

THANK YOU FOR YOUR FEEDBACK - WE WILL GET THESE MASKS ON ORDER!

post_text: ATTN: We still have 17 spots available for sports physicals on Tuesday, June 30th. To schedule your appointment call or text Nurse Becky at 785-488-6091
text: ATTN: We still have 17 spots available for sports physicals on Tuesday, June 30th. To schedule your appointment call or text Nurse Becky at 785-488-6091

post_text:
We will be offering sports physicals at Bennington & Tescott this year. Mindy Lovendahl APRN, will be at Bennington Tuesday, June 23rd from 7:30-12:00 & Tescott Tuesday, June 30th from 7:30-12:00. The physical will take place in the nurse’s office at both schools. The cost of the physical will be $15.00. If you are paying by check please make it out to either Bennington or Tescott High School. Funds collected will be donated to the schools. Physical forms will be mailed with report cards. Please be aware the physical forms have been updated this year. Mindy will not complete the physical if pages 1 & 2 are not filled out and parents be aware that you must also sign on pages 4 & 5.
Please call nurse Becky at 785-488-6091 to schedule a time slot.

*Remember you must bring payment and your physical form with you to your appointment. *

Optional Technology Return:

We have had a few parents request the option of being able to turn in the technology (Chromebook or IPad) this spring. For logistics and health reasons, we have decided to allow students to keep the technology over the summer but do understand there might be cases where that is not a tenable situation. If you want to return the IPad or Chromebooks, please email Mr. Pecenka at specenka@usd240.org or Sheila Fiske at sfiske@usd240.org to make those arrangements.

Twin Valley Usd 240
April 30 at 5:04 PM ·

Attention Twin Valley patrons. We have a company coming into the district to resurface the tracks in Bennington and Tescott during the months of May and early June. They will be starting in Bennington as early as Monday, May 4. After they are done there, they will proceed to Tescott and address that track. It will take approximately 3 weeks per location.

During the time the renovation, those areas will be off limits. We will announce when the public is allowed to begin using the tracks after the work is complete.

Contact Mr. Van Ranken if you have any questions or concerns. We are very excited to get these completed for Twin Valley kids next year!

post_text: Another learning opportunity for children and their families!
shared_text:
Kansas State Department of Education
April 17 at 9:46 PM ·

We are excited to announce that Kansas teachers, students and parents just got a new partner in their continuous learning efforts.

Thanks to the support of Kansas Public Broadcasters, Kansas students will receive supplemental education content by way of a new television program produced by Kansas PBS stations and KSDE, and hosted by local teachers. The new program called Learning Across Kansas will begin airing the week of April 20.

Each 30-minute segment, individually produced for elementary, middle school and high school students, will feature grade-specific educational content delivered by our very own Kansas teachers who serve on KSDE’s Continuous Learning Task Force.

Teachers, students and parents/caregivers, tune in for short, fun and engaging lessons. Plus, you just might see one of your own teachers presenting!

Learn more by visiting, https://www.ksde.org/Agency/Fiscal-and-Administrative-Services/Communications-and-Recognition-Programs/Learning-Across-Kansas

January 16 at 5:23 PM ·

January is School Board Appreciation Month. We want to thank you, USD 240 Board Members for your dedication and service: Warren McDougal-President, Rosemary Neaderhiser-Vice President, Robert Miller, Juanita Morris, Lorraine Pecenka, Ray Swearingen, Jeremiah Van Doren. #thankboe
